BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 96.96000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 4: Listing All Expenses) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Gather your bank statements and credit card bills from the last three months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Start with fixed expenses that stay the same: rent, car payment, insurance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Then list variable expenses that change: groceries, gas, utilities, dining out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Do not forget periodic expenses: annual subscriptions, car registration, gifts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Divide annual and quarterly expenses by twelve to get the monthly amount.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Check for forgotten subscriptions you signed up for and never cancelled.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (The average American has twelve paid subscriptions they may not all need.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Categorize expenses into needs, wants, and savings to see the big picture.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Be completely honest. Include every coffee, snack, and impulse purchase.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Use your bank app to categorize transactions automatically if available.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Most people are surprised to discover they spend more than they thought.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (This exercise alone often reveals hundreds in unnecessary spending.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (4) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
