BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 73.92000000000002 600 Td (Chapter 5: Creating Your First Budget) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start by writing your total monthly income at the top of a page.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (List all your expense categories below with estimated amounts for each.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Subtract total expenses from total income. The result should be zero or positive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (If negative, you are spending more than you earn and must cut something.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Assign every dollar a job so nothing is left unaccounted for.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (This is called zero-based budgeting and it is extremely effective.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Use categories that make sense for your life, not generic templates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Include a small miscellaneous category for unexpected small expenses.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Build in some buffer for categories that fluctuate like groceries.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Write your budget on paper, a spreadsheet, or a budgeting app.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Review and adjust your budget weekly for the first few months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A budget is a living document that improves each month as you learn.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (5) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
