BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 47.04000000000002 600 Td (Chapter 8: Paying Off Debt \(Snowball Method\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (The debt snowball method pays off debts from smallest to largest balance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (List all debts with their balances, minimum payments, and interest rates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Make minimum payments on all debts except the smallest one.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Throw every extra dollar at the smallest debt until it is completely gone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Once the smallest debt is paid off, add its payment to the next smallest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (This creates a snowball effect as your payment amount grows with each debt.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (The psychological wins of paying off small debts keep you motivated.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Some people prefer the avalanche method which targets highest interest first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (The avalanche saves more money mathematically but the snowball keeps you going.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Stop using credit cards while paying off debt to avoid digging deeper.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Celebrate each paid-off debt to maintain momentum and motivation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Most people can become debt-free in two to five years with focused effort.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
