BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 93.12 600 Td (Chapter 9: Saving for Retirement) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start saving for retirement as early as possible due to compound interest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (If your employer offers a 401k match, contribute at least enough to get it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (A company match is free money. Not taking it is leaving your pay on the table.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (After the match, consider a Roth IRA for tax-free growth on your money.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Aim to save fifteen percent of your gross income for retirement.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (If you cannot do fifteen percent now, start with what you can and increase yearly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Compound interest means your money earns money on top of money it already earned.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Starting at 25 with two hundred monthly can yield over half a million by 65.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Starting at 35 requires nearly double the monthly amount for the same result.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Choose low-cost index funds that track the entire market for simplicity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Do not try to time the market. Consistent investing over time always wins.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Retirement savings should be automated so you never have to think about it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (9) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
