BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 54.72 600 Td (Chapter 10: Budgeting for Irregular Income) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Irregular income includes freelance, commission, seasonal, and gig work.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Calculate your average monthly income from the past six to twelve months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Build a larger emergency fund of six months since income is unpredictable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Budget based on your lowest earning month to ensure you can always cover bills.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (In high-earning months, save the surplus in a buffer account.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Draw from the buffer during low-income months to smooth out fluctuations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Prioritize needs first: pay essential bills before anything else.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Create a priority list of expenses ranked from most to least important.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (When income is low, work down the list until the money runs out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Avoid lifestyle inflation during good months. Save the excess instead.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Consider diversifying income streams to reduce reliance on one source.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Irregular income makes budgeting harder but even more essential.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (10) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
