BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 89.28 600 Td (Chapter 11: Budgeting as a Couple) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Money is the number one cause of conflict in relationships.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Schedule regular money dates to discuss finances together without judgment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Decide whether to combine all money, keep separate, or use a hybrid system.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (A hybrid approach works well: shared account for bills, personal accounts for fun.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Set a spending threshold where either partner must consult the other first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Be transparent about debts, income, and financial goals with each other.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Assign money roles based on strengths: who pays bills, who tracks spending.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Create shared financial goals like a vacation, home, or debt payoff.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Respect different money personalities. One may be a saver and one a spender.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Compromise is key. Both partners should have some guilt-free spending money.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Review your budget together monthly and adjust as life changes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Working as a team on money builds trust and strengthens your relationship.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
