BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 73.92000000000002 600 Td (Chapter 12: Teaching Kids About Money) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start teaching money basics as early as age three or four.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Use three jars labeled Save, Spend, and Give for young children.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Give age-appropriate allowance tied to completing household chores.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Let children make spending mistakes with small amounts to learn consequences.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Take kids grocery shopping and show them how to compare prices.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Open a savings account for children and show them interest growing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Teach teens about compound interest using simple examples and charts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Involve teenagers in family budget discussions appropriate for their age.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Help teens earn their own money through babysitting, lawn care, or tutoring.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Discuss wants versus needs regularly in everyday situations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Model good financial behavior because children learn from what they see.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Teaching kids about money is one of the greatest gifts you can give them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (12) Tj ET

endstream
