BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 13: Apps and Tools That Help) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Mint is a free app that connects to your accounts and categorizes spending.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (YNAB \(You Need A Budget\) teaches zero-based budgeting with excellent support.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (EveryDollar is a simple drag-and-drop budgeting app by Dave Ramsey.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Personal Capital is best for tracking investments and net worth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Goodbudget uses the digital envelope system for couples budgeting together.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (A simple spreadsheet in Google Sheets or Excel works perfectly fine too.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (The best tool is the one you will actually use consistently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Set up automatic bill payments to avoid late fees and missed payments.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Use your bank app to set up alerts for low balances and large purchases.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Cash envelope system works for people who overspend with cards.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Try a few different apps to find what matches your style.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Technology makes budgeting faster but the principles remain the same.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (13) Tj ET

endstream
