q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Mistake one: making your budget too restrictive with zero fun money.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Mistake two: not tracking small purchases that add up significantly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Mistake three: forgetting irregular expenses like car maintenance and gifts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Mistake four: giving up after one bad month instead of adjusting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Mistake five: not involving your partner in the budgeting process.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Mistake six: budgeting based on gross income instead of take-home pay.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Mistake seven: not having a miscellaneous category for unexpected costs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Mistake eight: comparing your budget to others instead of your own goals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Mistake nine: treating the budget as a set-it-and-forget-it document.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Mistake ten: not celebrating small wins and progress along the way.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Every budgeter makes mistakes. The key is to learn and adjust each month.) Tj ET
