BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 15: Your 30-Day Action Plan) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Day 1: Calculate your exact monthly take-home income from all sources.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Days 2-3: Review three months of bank and credit card statements.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Days 4-5: List and categorize every recurring expense you have.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Day 6: Cancel at least two subscriptions or services you do not use.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Day 7: Create your first monthly budget using the 50/30/20 framework.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Days 8-14: Track every single purchase you make, no matter how small.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Day 15: Review your tracking and adjust budget categories as needed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Days 16-18: Set up automatic transfers to savings, even if just 25 dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Days 19-21: Call one bill provider and negotiate a lower rate.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Days 22-25: Open a separate high-yield savings account for emergencies.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Days 26-28: Research and choose a budgeting app or system that fits you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Days 29-30: Review your progress, celebrate wins, and plan next month.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (15) Tj ET

